  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 2 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 high, 6 medium, 27 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Modlin (WMI/EPMO) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI); plus 3 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk and mist  — most notably around Catania-Fontanarossa (CTA/LICC), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO). Network hotspots: Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Billund (BLL/EKBI) and 9 others.",
